Brand new location, same great food!  BK Jani outdoes itself every time I take a bite/sip of their delicious offerings because it never disappoints. Their delicious patties, a special halal blend of the famous Pat La Frieda, is enhanced by their special spicy green chutney, so be careful of the spice levels you can handle. The lamb chops are a different epic altogether that I make sure I devour till the bone is bare. The "Masala Fries brings back a lot of memories of growing up in Pakistan when the solution to all issues with blandness was "Chaat Masala". In drinks, DO NOT skip over the "Limeade" and the "Mango Jani" which (with its use of Black Salt?) brings out the true experience of a street-side vendor refreshment in the sweltering summers. At a previous visit I also happened to make a skeptical adventure upon the "Nihari Sandwich" and much to my surprise if there was a way to do it right, they did it perfectly!  Beyond the food, their new Grand Street location has the perfect vibe and decor for the comfortable and casual "hanging-out" over bench-style seating next to vibrant wall art. What is more, I got to get a sneak-peak of their soon-to-open back yard space which I can just imagine will take lounging over food to the next level, Pakistani style!

This didn’t make any sense at all. Clearly if people are getting fries with a burger, one charges them the price for a side. Who is going to eat as many fries as if you didn’t have a burger or sandwich per person in the party! The net difference is only $2/portion but it just feels like an unneeded hustle.

I for one have tried many burgers around NYC and I only thought highly of one place but have been trying out many places to see if I can add another favorite to the list, for years! Look man don't look any further - this has now become my new favorite spot - trumping the old one. I told Jani - it was like my favorite one was missing a formula I didn't even think was needed and Jani just happend to have the potion! F'ing juicy, flavorful and will catch you off guard. I won't stir you wrong - definitely go check them out and order your burger spicy and medium rare - don't be a punk! Found! I ventured to Bushwick with friends to Bk Jani. Expectations were high and they were exceeded. It is a Pakistani restaurant that simply takes the best cuts of meat from Pat LaFreida, seasons them correctly, and cooks them perfectly. That's it and the results are stunning. The place is almost cafeteria-like and the food is served on paper plates. There is really no need to order as the owner brings you what you should eat. There really is nothing but meat: Lamb chops, steak, and the hamburger! The seasoning is a mixture of mint and spices that stimulate the taste buds without overwhelming them. There is an amazing consistency to meats prepared well that may have changed how I think about meats going forward. This place is a must! For more great reviews visit TheLoupe!
